all fucking night, okay?

94
00:07:09,962 --> 00:07:11,896
There's enough drug money in there...

95
00:07:11,964 --> 00:07:15,695
that we're gonna need
a fucking wheelbarrow to carry it out.

96
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:17,702
So stop messing around.

97
00:07:20,573 --> 00:07:23,133
I mean, you got a game
those people never seen.

98
00:07:24,076 --> 00:07:27,512
And quite frankly,
I'd like to see it sometime myself tonight.

99
00:07:28,881 --> 00:07:32,442
You're gonna go in there,
you're gonna bump up the bet...

100
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:35,617
and you're gonna
close this fucking night out.

101
00:07:36,322 --> 00:07:38,654
So stop wasting my fucking time.

102
00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:42,192
Just do it.

103
00:07:50,503 --> 00:07:51,765
A bottle of Jack.

104
00:07:51,838 --> 00:07:56,138
I'll be a three-legged dog
if I'm not looking at the Side Pocket Kid.

105
00:07:56,442 --> 00:07:57,602
You don't remember me...

106
00:07:57,677 --> 00:08:00,612
but I saw you play once
about 10 or 15 years ago.

107
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:03,539
I used to wear a rug.

108
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:06,011
Toupee Jay.

109
00:08:06,118 --> 00:08:07,710
Yeah, that's me.

110
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:11,715
I saw this kid play one of the best games
I've ever seen in my life.

111
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:14,282
Couldn't have been more than
14 or 15 years old...

112
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:17,124
but, man, he could shoot the lights out!

113
00:08:17,396 --> 00:08:19,694
Now look at him. He's all grown up.

114
00:08:21,434 --> 00:08:24,062
You know, I always wondered
what happened to you.

115
00:08:24,136 --> 00:08:26,468
Why you never made it down
to Johnson City.

116
00:08:26,539 --> 00:08:29,702
Well, Jay, I've never been
much of a tournament player.

117
00:08:29,775 --> 00:08:32,175
-There's no money in them.
-No money?

118
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:36,610
We just held the U.S. Open in Atlanta.
First prize was $100,000.

119
00:08:39,285 --> 00:08:42,345
But you gotta be invited to those things,
don't you?

120
00:08:42,421 --> 00:08:46,824
We did invite you. A couple of times.
I sent the invitations out myself.

121
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:52,157
I even called and spoke to a backer
you had in those days.

122
00:08:52,431 --> 00:08:55,594
But he said you weren't interested.
Something about...

123
00:08:56,068 --> 00:08:59,060
your parents wanting you to finish school.

124
00:08:59,672 --> 00:09:02,903
What was the name
of that backer you had, anyway?

125
00:09:05,311 --> 00:09:06,642
Was it Joe?

126
00:09:09,882 --> 00:09:11,349
Bet $20,000!

127
00:09:13,452 --> 00:09:15,784
What's the matter? Did I stutter?

128
00:09:16,088 --> 00:09:18,283
Everybody got all quiet, and shit?

129
00:09:18,357 --> 00:09:21,485
About a minute ago,
it was like an evening at the Apollo.

130
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,428
Now, all of a sudden, it's quiet as a church.

131
00:09:25,865 --> 00:09:28,265
That's all right, Chico, I don't blame you.

132
00:09:28,634 --> 00:09:32,832
I've been beating this motherfucker
all goddamn night. He can't win.

133
00:09:33,205 --> 00:09:35,298
You better watch your mouth.

134
00:09:35,374 --> 00:09:37,205
You watch my mouth, Chico...

135
00:09:37,276 --> 00:09:40,109
'cause you sure as hell
don't want to watch me play pool.

136
00:09:40,179 --> 00:09:43,546
Unless I'm blindfolded, handcuffed,
with a cue sticking out of my ass.

137
00:09:43,616 --> 00:09:46,176
Maybe you'd bet the $20,000 then, right?

138
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:49,920
That's what I thought.

139
00:09:52,024 --> 00:09:54,390
Come on, Joe, let's get the fuck out of here.

140
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:57,224
These guys wouldn't bet $5 they were black.

141
00:09:57,897 --> 00:09:59,194
Hold this.

142
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,097
You got a bet.

143
00:10:02,568 --> 00:10:06,527
But for $20,000, you got to play
my man Brad in the corner, over there.

144
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:12,673
What are you doing?
I only got $8,000 on me.

145
00:10:12,745 --> 00:10:16,875
Don't play that guy. He's a pro.
I saw him at the pro tournament in Phoenix.

146
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:19,440
Don't you ever tell me who I play again.

147
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:24,013
I'll play anybody in the house,
you know that, Chico.

148
00:10:26,058 --> 00:10:28,856
Do you wanna play this bad motherfucker
on my money?

149
00:10:28,928 --> 00:10:30,520
I don't think so.

150
00:10:30,696 --> 00:10:32,891
Seems you got
too much personal shit going on.

151
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:36,401
You know what? Fuck you, Johnny.
Charles, get the rack.

152
00:10:36,769 --> 00:10:38,031
I'll play him myself.

153
00:11:16,942 --> 00:11:20,776
-What the fuck are you doing?
-He's got $8,000 on him, but it's not enough.

154
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,780
What the fuck is going on?

155
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:25,339
You should have looked out for me.
I was just a kid.

156
00:11:25,418 --> 00:11:28,080
I'll fucking kill you, you motherfucker!

157
00:11:28,154 --> 00:11:29,621
Shut the fuck up!

158
00:11:30,156 --> 00:11:34,525
Do you honestly think that I would let
a white boy walk into my pool hall...

159
00:11:34,593 --> 00:11:37,721
and talk that much shit
unless he was trying to tell me something?

160
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:40,027
You missed the fucking signs.

161
00:11:41,133 --> 00:11:42,725
You didn't listen.

162
00:11:42,802 --> 00:11:44,997
Me and Johnny, we's niggas.

163
00:11:47,073 --> 00:11:49,098
-I'm out of here.
-Peace.

164
00:11:49,508 --> 00:11:52,671
What's this I hear
about you not having my money?

165
00:11:55,848 --> 00:11:57,611
Get the fuck off me!

166
00:12:06,358 --> 00:12:08,383
When I was 12, I walked into a pool room...

167
00:12:08,461 --> 00:12:10,656
picked up a cue,
and I just knew how to play.

168
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:13,528
I guess, for some people,
it's baseball or music.

169
00:12:13,599 --> 00:12:15,396
For me, it was pool.

170
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:19,234
But I never wanted to be a hustler.
I wanted to be the best.

171
00:12:20,139 --> 00:12:22,403
But after 15 years with Joe...

172
00:12:22,475 --> 00:12:25,444
the only thing I ever got to be
was the best hustler.

173
00:12:25,511 --> 00:12:29,174
I guess, in life, things don't always work out
the way you want them to.

174
00:14:05,044 --> 00:14:06,534
You wanted to see me?

175
00:14:07,947 --> 00:14:11,906
I'd have to say you're the worst carpenter
I ever worked with in my entire life.

176
00:14:11,984 --> 00:14:13,451
How did you get this job?

177
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:15,419
Jack Radosta hired me on.

178
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:19,150
