1173
01:20:27,889 --> 01:20:30,983
-What's it worth to you?
-I paid $2,800 for it.

1174
01:20:31,760 --> 01:20:33,387
$3,000. Covered.

1175
01:20:35,964 --> 01:20:40,367
I'm gonna leave you with nothing.
Nick, make sure, please, it's all there.

1176
01:20:40,869 --> 01:20:43,463
I'm gonna have a drink. You want a drink?

1177
01:20:45,473 --> 01:20:46,633
All right.

1178
01:21:03,024 --> 01:21:06,221
You watch those nature documentaries
on the cable?

1179
01:21:07,229 --> 01:21:08,253
Yeah.

1180
01:21:08,330 --> 01:21:10,298
See the one about lions?

1181
01:21:13,134 --> 01:21:14,829
Got this lion.

1182
01:21:15,570 --> 01:21:19,506
He's the king of the jungle.
Huge mane, out to here.

1183
01:21:20,175 --> 01:21:23,872
He's laying down under a tree,
in the middle of Africa.

1184
01:21:24,346 --> 01:21:27,406
He's so big. He's so hot.

1185
01:21:29,251 --> 01:21:31,219
He doesn't want to move.

1186
01:21:32,187 --> 01:21:35,384
The little lion cubs,
they start messing with him.

1187
01:21:36,024 --> 01:21:39,755
Biting his tail, biting his ears.
He doesn't do anything.

1188
01:21:41,029 --> 01:21:44,362
The lioness, she starts messing with him...

1189
01:21:44,666 --> 01:21:48,500
coming over, making trouble. Still nothing.

1190
01:21:49,037 --> 01:21:51,870
Now, the other animals notice this...

1191
01:21:53,008 --> 01:21:56,068
and they start to move in, the jackals.

1192
01:21:57,746 --> 01:21:58,940
Hyenas.

1193
01:21:59,848 --> 01:22:02,373
They're barking at him, laughing at him.

1194
01:22:03,151 --> 01:22:07,485
They nip his toes
and eat the food that's in his domain.

1195
01:22:07,989 --> 01:22:09,456
They do this...

1196
01:22:09,524 --> 01:22:13,927
then they get closer and bolder,
till one day...

1197
01:22:15,563 --> 01:22:18,828
that lion gets up
and tears the shit out of everybody...

1198
01:22:18,900 --> 01:22:22,427
runs like the wind,
eats everything in his path.

1199
01:22:23,071 --> 01:22:27,405
'Cause every once in a while,
the lion has to show the jackals...

1200
01:22:29,878 --> 01:22:31,209
who he is.

1201
01:22:36,284 --> 01:22:39,879
It's too late to be scared. It's time to kill.

1202
01:22:41,323 --> 01:22:45,054
I'm going in the other room.
You come out when you're ready.

1203
01:22:49,831 --> 01:22:52,800
Don't beat him. Kick his ass.

1204
01:24:30,665 --> 01:24:32,758
Watch this 2-ball go down.

1205
01:25:10,839 --> 01:25:11,931
Fuck.

1206
01:25:12,540 --> 01:25:15,839
That's fucking bullshit!
I can't fucking believe this.

1207
01:25:18,279 --> 01:25:22,511
I don't know. I think I gotta bank it.
There's nothing else I can do.

1208
01:25:22,951 --> 01:25:25,613
You can do it. It's a two-rail safety.

1209
01:25:26,187 --> 01:25:28,678
I think you're right. Thanks, Nick.

1210
01:25:46,641 --> 01:25:47,938
Good shot.

1211
01:26:01,256 --> 01:26:03,986
Take that, you motherless motherfuckers!

1212
01:26:04,325 --> 01:26:07,294
Stop. Easy. No....

1213
01:26:08,429 --> 01:26:09,521
Shit!

1214
01:26:28,516 --> 01:26:31,041
Shoot the shot already. It's an easy shot.

1215
01:26:31,119 --> 01:26:34,418
-Easy shot, my ass.
-Shows how much you know.

1216
01:26:34,489 --> 01:26:37,390
I can't believe I'm playing
with somebody so fucking stupid.

1217
01:26:37,458 --> 01:26:41,053
I ain't biting on any of your
South Side shark techniques, so shut up.

1218
01:26:41,129 --> 01:26:42,721
The shot can't be made, Brad.

1219
01:26:42,797 --> 01:26:45,231
Believe me,
I'd rather have you shoot it than me.

1220
01:26:45,300 --> 01:26:46,528
Me, too.

1221
01:26:51,506 --> 01:26:53,235
-Come on!
-Bullshit.

1222
01:26:53,341 --> 01:26:56,367
If you think it's so easy,
why don't you come and shoot it?

1223
01:26:56,444 --> 01:27:00,244
Believe me, I wish I could.
I'd pay to shoot a shot like that.

1224
01:27:01,249 --> 01:27:03,979
How much is it worth to you, Johnny boy?

1225
01:27:04,452 --> 01:27:05,851
What are you saying?

1226
01:27:05,920 --> 01:27:09,822
You think you can make it. I say
it can't be made. I don't want him doing it.

1227
01:27:09,891 --> 01:27:13,452
So why don't you speak to Daddy Warbucks
and see how much it's worth?

1228
01:27:13,528 --> 01:27:17,328
I don't gotta ask nobody nothing.
That's a tough fucking shot.

1229
01:27:17,398 --> 01:27:19,662
It's worth, maybe, $200 bucks.

1230
01:27:20,468 --> 01:27:24,802
$200? We're playing for $100,000
and you want to offer me $200?

1231
01:27:25,607 --> 01:27:28,599
Offer me $5,000,
and then maybe I'll think about it.

1232
01:27:28,676 --> 01:27:30,473
What are you saying, Joe?

1233
01:27:30,545 --> 01:27:34,174
You don't want to go home broke
once John makes this shot.

1234
01:27:34,716 --> 01:27:36,980
Listen, mister, all due respect...

1235
01:27:37,051 --> 01:27:39,815
but save your money,
'cause you don't know the game.

1236
01:27:39,887 --> 01:27:41,821
The shot can't be made.

1237
01:27:42,624 --> 01:27:44,148
It's up to you.

1238
01:27:46,494 --> 01:27:48,359
Here's your gas money.

1239
01:27:49,664 --> 01:27:51,256
You're gonna need it.

1240
01:27:51,366 --> 01:27:52,628
Excuse me.

1241
01:28:03,278 --> 01:28:05,542
Come on, get legs.

1242
01:28:08,383 --> 01:28:09,475
Fuck!

1243
01:28:11,686 --> 01:28:15,713
What the hell were you thinking?
I told you you couldn't make the shot.

1244
01:28:20,428 --> 01:28:23,158
-What are you doing?
-I'm taking my shot.

1245
01:28:26,301 --> 01:28:30,362
See, I just paid $5,000 for your shot.

1246
01:28:31,172 --> 01:28:32,434
Now it's my shot.

1247
01:28:35,376 --> 01:28:37,139
Listen, you can't do that.

1248
01:28:39,480 --> 01:28:41,414
-He just did.
-This is bullshit!

1249
01:28:41,482 --> 01:28:44,246
It's not an old trick
you should have been looking out for.

1250
01:28:44,319 --> 01:28:48,619
-This is fucking bullshit, man!
-Here's what my brother owes you.

1251
01:28:48,690 --> 01:28:51,989
-Fuck you.
-You and I got some unfinished business.

1252
01:28:52,093 --> 01:28:56,029
The rest of y'all clear out.
It's about to get rowdy in this motherfucker.

1253
01:28:58,499 --> 01:29:00,763
-Go!
-Later, Joe.

1254
01:29:13,314 --> 01:29:15,373
A game like that, you should be on the tour.

1255
01:29:16,184 --> 01:29:19,017
I don't think you'd want me beating you
every week.

1256
01:29:19,087 --> 01:29:21,521
You didn't beat me. I got hustled.

1257
01:29:23,691 --> 01:29:26,216
Maybe you did, and maybe you didn't.

1258
01:29:26,494 --> 01:29:29,952
-I guess I'm a hustler.
-Doesn't have to stay that way.

1259
01:29:30,631 --> 01:29:32,155
Think about it.

1260
01:29:49,384 --> 01:29:51,147
Wanna get out of here?

1261
01:29:52,220 --> 01:29:54,085
Let's go get your brother.

1262
01:29:54,155 --> 01:29:56,988
-Wait, we're not going in that.
-What are we going in?

1263
01:29:57,058 --> 01:29:58,821
We're going in that.

1264
01:30:00,194 --> 01:30:02,788
That's my Uncle Mike's car.

1265
01:30:03,865 --> 01:30:05,992
Not anymore. Come on.

1266
01:30:27,655 --> 01:30:29,680
Okay, boys, you ready?

1267
01:30:36,130 --> 01:30:37,119
Go.

1268
01:31:03,458 --> 01:31:06,427
Give me two seconds.... Okay, I'm all right!

1269
01:31:07,061 --> 01:31:08,528
Jesus Christ.

1270
01:31:15,369 --> 01:31:18,167
-I'm telling you, right now--
-No way those are real.

1271
01:31:18,239 --> 01:31:20,366
What we need is a plastic surgeon.

1272
01:31:20,475 --> 01:31:23,774
Shut up! We need a consensus,
all right? Tang?

1273
01:31:23,845 --> 01:31:26,575
They must be real. There's no scar.
I'm going with God.

1274
01:31:26,647 --> 01:31:29,047
Are you retarded?
There's laser technology now.

1275
01:31:29,116 --> 01:31:32,574
They can remove scars, plus God made
plastic surgery. 100-percent fake.

1276
01:31:32,653 --> 01:31:35,588
I don't know. It's a shot in the dark,
but I'll go with real.

1277
01:31:35,656 --> 01:31:39,387
I can't leave Max hanging on this.
They look great, but a little too amazing.

1278
01:31:39,460 --> 01:31:40,984
I'll say store-bought.

1279
01:31:49,337 --> 01:31:52,306
All right! Is that your final answer?

1280
01:31:53,641 --> 01:31:56,371
Want to take the 50-50? Audience choice?

1281
01:31:56,744 --> 01:31:58,575
-Come on.
-All right, okay!

1282
01:31:59,213 --> 01:32:02,148
All right, Scarlet.
Here's the moment of truth.

1283
01:32:02,216 --> 01:32:05,617
-Are they real, or are they Memorex?
-They're real.

1284
01:32:07,688 --> 01:32:08,712
I knew it!

1285
01:32:08,789 --> 01:32:12,850
-Scarlet, they feel hard as a rock.
-Never go swimming. You'll drown.

